<collectingCountry id="F366766BFF9E2519FB93729AFB2B5DEA" box="[1114,1169,945,971]" name="Peru" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE36FBFF9E2519FF0E72FEFC395B2E" blockId="17.[151,1437,153,1295]" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FF0E72FEFE8E5DCE" bold="true" box="[199,308,981,1007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Remarks</emphasis>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B0AFF9E2519FE1672FEFCBC5DCE" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[479,774,981,1007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" pagination="571 - 580" refId="ref20646" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2013) New species and records of Cerambycinae and Lamiinae (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) from the Neotropical Region. Zootaxa, 3683 (5), 571 - 580. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3683.5. 5" type="journal article" year="2013">Martins &amp; Galileo (2013)</bibRefCitation>
: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FCD672FEFB975DCE" authority="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark, 2019" authorityName="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2019" box="[799,1069,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidicolor" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FCD672FEFB975DCE" box="[799,1069,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Pteroplatus pallidicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2365792FF9E2519FBFC72FEFB325DCE" box="[1077,1160,981,1007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species">sp. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FA4172FDFEA05A32" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FA4172FDFEA05A32" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">P. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B0AFF9E2519FEE872D2FE0F5A32" author="Breme, F." box="[289,437,1016,1043]" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" pagination="287 - 313" refId="ref18777" refString="Breme, F. (1845) Insectes coleopteres nouveaux ou peu connus. Premiere et deuxieme decades. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 2 (2), 287 - 313." type="journal article" year="1845">Brême, 1845</bibRefCitation>
, described from 
<collectingCountry id="F366766BFF9E2519FDB872D2FD585A32" box="[625,738,1017,1043]" name="Colombia" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, by the two black spots close to the base of the pronotum, and by the black scutellum. In 
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FE097535FDDF5A16" box="[448,613,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FE097535FDDB5A16" box="[448,609,1054,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">P. nigriventris</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the pronotum has three longitudinal black stripes, one central and one on each side and scutellum yellow.” However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FDB37569FCA25A7A" authorityName="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2019" box="[634,792,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidicolor">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FDB37569FCA25A7A" box="[634,792,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">P. pallidicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is noticeably different from the 
<typeStatus id="54CA8859FF9E2519FBB3756AFB665A7A" box="[1146,1244,1089,1115]" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FB367569FA275A7A" box="[1279,1437,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FB367569FA275A7A" box="[1279,1437,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">P. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the elytral shape and sculpturing. Furthermore, the 
<typeStatus id="54CA8859FF9E2519FD22754EFCF75A5E" box="[747,845,1125,1151]" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">holotype</typeStatus>
of the latter has a single longitudinal black band, and not three. 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FEC275A2FDA35A82" authorityName="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2019" box="[267,537,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidicolor">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FEC275A2FDA35A82" box="[267,537,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Pteroplatus pallidicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FD2475A1FCDD5A82" authorityName="Belon" authorityYear="1903" box="[749,871,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchora">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FD2475A1FCDD5A82" box="[749,871,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">P. anchora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, practically only differing by the elytra not being reticulate. The anterior area of the prothorax is wider than the posterior margin in the 
<typeStatus id="54CA8859FF9E2519FBA37586FB765AE6" box="[1130,1228,1197,1223]" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FB3D7585FA2F5AE6" authorityName="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2019" box="[1268,1429,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidicolor">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FB3D7585FA2F5AE6" box="[1268,1429,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">P. pallidicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, this kind of variation was observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FD7D75F9FC2B5ACA" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1880" box="[692,913,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriscopulatus">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FD7D75F9FC2B5ACA" box="[692,913,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">P. quadriscopulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, probably, may also occur in specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D78FF9E2519FF5E75DDFEAA5B2E" authorityName="Belon" authorityYear="1903" box="[151,272,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchora">
<emphasis id="B905EAE9FF9E2519FF5E75DDFEAA5B2E" box="[151,272,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">P. anchora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Accordingly, it cannot be used as a differential feature.
</paragraph>
